# Timeline

Chronological list of events.

## Basic Usage
### Timeline
Highlight recent updates.
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="TimelineTimelineDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <template>
    <TxTimeline>
      <TxTimelineItem title="Design phase" time="09:30" color="primary" />
      <TxTimelineItem title="Build" time="12:00" color="success" />
      <TxTimelineItem title="Launch" time="16:10" color="warning" />
    </TxTimeline>
  </template>
---
:::
## API (Lite)
### TxTimeline Props
::TuffPropsTable
---
rows:
  - name: layout
    type: "'vertical' | 'horizontal'"
    default: "'vertical'"
    description: Layout direction
---
:::

### TxTimelineItem Props
::TuffPropsTable
---
rows:
  - name: title
    type: string
    default: "''"
    description: Timeline item title
  - name: time
    type: string
    default: "''"
    description: Time label
  - name: color
    type: "'default' | 'primary' | 'success' | 'warning' | 'error'"
    default: "'default'"
    description: Dot color
  - name: icon
    type: string
    default: '-'
    description: Dot icon
  - name: active
    type: boolean
    default: 'false'
    description: Highlight the current event item
---
:::

## Interaction Contract

- `TxTimeline` exposes `role="list"` and each `TxTimelineItem` exposes `role="listitem"`.
- `active` applies to both the item and dot, highlighting the current event.
- `layout="horizontal"` is provided to child items through context, switching the event stream to a horizontal layout.

